App Library - Drawing and Text Editor
This simple web application allows users to draw, change colors, highlight, erase, and add text to a canvas. It is built using HTML5, Tailwind CSS, and Font Awesome, with a JavaScript-driven interface for handling drawing and text functionalities.

Features
Drawing: Freehand drawing on the canvas with selectable colors (red, blue, green, black).
Highlighter: Highlight areas with semi-transparent yellow color.
Eraser: Clear the drawing or reset the canvas.
Text Box: Add and edit text on the canvas.
Download: Download the canvas as a PNG image.
Responsive UI: Built with Tailwind CSS for responsiveness and easy customization.
Technologies Used
HTML5: Provides the basic structure and functionality.
Tailwind CSS: Utility-first CSS framework used for styling the elements.
Font Awesome: Used for iconography (e.g., eraser, highlighter).
JavaScript: For handling drawing and interaction with the canvas element.
Setup
Clone the repository or create an HTML file with the code provided below.
Include external libraries for Tailwind CSS and Font Awesome as shown in the <head> section.
Run the HTML file in any modern web browser to interact with the app.